  "texts": [
    "As a result, participants were less confident in the completeness of their outlines.",
    "This can be confirmed by the observation that the HINTs group participants felt more time pressure than the Baseline Group as suggested by the difference in Temporal Demand.",
    "In addition, when the participants were asked in the interview \"If given more time, what would you do to perfect the literature review outline?",
    "\", the Baseline Group participants mostly wanted to do further verification, while the HINTs group participants considered further investigation on certain sub-topics or techniques, suggesting awareness of the incompleteness of the outline.",
    "B. Commonalities In Comparative Behavior PatternsBeyond the evaluation of the system, we report insights on the comparative behavior patterns to contribute to a better understanding of the sensemaking challenges with the help (14)(15)(16)(17)(18)(19)(20)(21)."
